### Hadith 1:802

*Narrated Abu Ma'bad:*

(the freed slave of Ibn 'Abbas) Ibn 'Abbas told me, "In the lifetime of
the Prophet it was the custom to celebrate Allah's praises aloud after
the compulsory congregational prayers." Ibn 'Abbas further said, "When I
heard the Dhikr, I would learn that the compulsory congregational prayer
had ended."

